# Responsible Disclosure Policy

At comma-separated, we take the security of our systems and data seriously. We value the contributions of security researchers and are committed to working with the community to identify and resolve vulnerabilities in a responsible and timely manner.

## Reporting a Vulnerability

If you believe you have found a security vulnerability in one of our systems, services, or products, please contact us at:

**Email:** security@comma-separated.com  

Please provide as much information as possible, including:

- A clear description of the vulnerability
- Steps to reproduce the issue
- Potential impact
- Any relevant logs, screenshots, or proof-of-concept code

## What to Expect

- We will acknowledge your report within 5 business days.
- We will provide regular updates on the status of your report.
- We will work to validate and fix the vulnerability as quickly as possible.
- With your permission, we may credit you on our Hall of Fame page.

## Guidelines

We kindly ask that you:

- Do not access, modify, or delete data that does not belong to you.
- Do not perform any actions that could impact the availability or integrity of our services (e.g., DoS attacks).
- Do not publicly disclose the vulnerability until we have resolved the issue.

We will not take legal action against individuals who report vulnerabilities responsibly and in good faith.

## Scope

This policy applies to vulnerabilities in:

- Web applications under the comma-separated.com domain
- Public APIs provided by comma-separated
- Mobile applications officially released by comma-separated

This policy does *not* apply to:

- Social engineering or phishing attacks
- Third-party services or applications not under our direct control

## Thank You

We appreciate the time and effort of researchers who help improve our security. Thank you for helping us keep our systems safe!

